sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS IAM
    participant Registry as Model Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ODHModel as ODH Model Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Knative as Knative Serving<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>mTLS
    participant Istio as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.3
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Client as External Client<br/>HTTPS

    Note over User,Dashboard: Phase 1: Development Environment Setup
    User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook (Jupyter/VS Code)<br/>HTTPS POST /api/notebooks
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Deploy StatefulSet<br/>with workbench image
    Notebook-->>User: Notebook Ready<br/>Route URL provided

    Note over User,S3: Phase 2: Model Training
    User->>Notebook: Develop & train model<br/>SSH/HTTPS session
    Notebook->>S3: Save trained model<br/>HTTPS PUT<br/>AWS Signature V4
    Notebook->>Registry: Register model metadata<br/>POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models

    Note over User,Predictor: Phase 3: Model Deployment
    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService<br/>HTTPS POST
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    KServe->>Knative: Create Knative Service<br/>serverless mode
    KServe->>ODHModel: Trigger reconciliation<br/>CR watch event
    ODHModel->>Istio: Create VirtualService & Gateway<br/>Kubernetes API
    ODHModel->>Dashboard: Create Route<br/>route.openshift.io API
    ODHModel->>Dashboard: Create ServiceMonitor<br/>monitoring.coreos.com API

    Note over Predictor,S3: Phase 4: Model Loading
    Knative->>Predictor: Create predictor pod<br/>on first request or scheduled
    Predictor->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>storage-initializer<br/>HTTPS GET<br/>AWS IAM
    S3-->>Predictor: Model files
    Predictor->>Predictor: Load model into memory<br/>framework-specific

    Note over Client,Predictor: Phase 5: Inference Serving
    Client->>Istio: POST /v2/models/model:infer<br/>HTTPS<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    Istio->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>HTTP<br/>mTLS (service mesh)
    Predictor->>Registry: Fetch model metadata (optional)<br/>gRPC
    Predictor->>Predictor: Run inference<br/>in-memory prediction
    Predictor-->>Istio: JSON response<br/>mTLS
    Istio-->>Client: HTTPS response<br/>TLS 1.3

    Note over TrustyAI,Predictor: Phase 6: Model Monitoring (Optional)
    User->>Dashboard: Create TrustyAIService<br/>HTTPS POST
    Dashboard->>TrustyAI: Deploy TrustyAI<br/>Kubernetes API
    TrustyAI->>KServe: Patch InferenceService<br/>add payload logging
    Predictor->>TrustyAI: Log predictions<br/>HTTP POST<br/>request/response payloads
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Analyze for bias/drift<br/>LIME/SHAP explanations
    User->>TrustyAI: Request explanations<br/>HTTPS GET /q/metrics

    Note over User,Client: End-to-End Flow Complete
